Identifier mapping for GTEx

ensembl <- useMart("ensembl")
ensembl = useDataset("hsapiens_gene_ensembl",mart=ensembl)

 conversion_stash <- "gtex_id_conversion.rds"
if(file.exists(conversion_stash)){
  gtex_id_conversion <- readRDS(conversion_stash)
} else {
  gtex_id_conversion <- getBM(attributes = c("ensembl_gene_id_version","hgnc_symbol"),
                            filters = "ensembl_gene_id_version",
                            values = rownames(gtex_data),
                            mart = ensembl)
  saveRDS(gtex_id_conversion, conversion_stash)
}

# merge
gtex_data_annot <- merge(gtex_id_conversion,gtex_data,by.x = 1, by.y = 0, all.y=TRUE)
write.table(gtex_data_annot, "/Users/helending/Documents/BCB330/gtex/data/gtex_annotated.csv")

# how many unmapped?

filter GTEx as expressed / not expressed

gtex_data_annot <- gtex_data_annot_copy

threshold <- 5
y <- gtex_data_annot[,3:ncol(gtex_data_annot)]
for(i in 1:nrow(y)){
  for (j in 1:ncol(y)){
    if (y[i, j] >= threshold){
      y[i, j] <- 1
    } else{
      y[i, j] <- 0
    }
  }
}
copy_y <- cbind("hgnc_symbol"=gtex_data_annot$hgnc_symbol, y)
copy_y <- cbind("ensembl_gene_id"=gtex_data_annot$ensembl_gene_id, copy_y)
write.table(copy_y, "/Users/helending/Documents/BCB330/gtex/data/filtered_gtex.csv")

IID

gene-gene interaction

  • Get IID human annotated PPIs (Kotlyar et al. 2019) genes, convert the two column gene-gene interactions into one column by copying and pasting one column to the bottom of the other column. And then we removed duplicates and write to the file: gene_interaction_dup.csv, and saved in the data folder.
IID_data <- read.delim("/Users/helending/Documents/BCB330/mir_expr_table/data/human_annotated_PPIs.txt", header = TRUE, sep = "\t")
gene_interaction <- IID_data
nrow(gene_interaction) # 975877
gene_interaction_copy <- gene_interaction
gene_interaction_copy[,c(1:4)] <- gene_interaction_copy[, c(1, 2, 4, 3)]

# bind the same table under the existing one, flip, and delete the "symbol 2" column
gene_interaction <- rbind(gene_interaction, gene_interaction_copy)

gene_interaction <- gene_interaction[,-c(1, 2, 4)]
colnames(gene_interaction)[1] <- "SYMBOLS"
gene_interaction <- gene_interaction[, -c(2, 3, 4, 5)]

# Remove duplicates
duplicated_genes <- which(duplicated(gene_interaction[1])) # 18726 unique genes
gene_interaction_dup <- gene_interaction
gene_interaction_dup <- gene_interaction_dup[-duplicated_genes,]
nrow(gene_interaction_dup) # 18726
write.table(gene_interaction_dup, "/Users/helending/Documents/BCB330/mir_expr_table/data/gene_interaction_dup.csv")

  miR_expr[,i]<- (as.character(miR_expr[,i]))
}
miR_expr[miR_expr == "?"] <- "10"
for (i in 2:ncol(miR_expr)){
  miR_expr[,i]<- (as.numeric(miR_expr[,i]))
}

new_mir <- left_join(final_table_copy_mir, miR_expr, by=c("miRNA" ="miRNA"))
new_mir <- new_mir[, -c(2:246)]
colnames(new)[2:ncol(new)] <- colnames(IID_data)[9:ncol(IID_data)]

Combine the two

new_mir_num <- miR_expr[,2:ncol(miR_expr)]
new_num <- new[,2:ncol(new)]

new_sum <- Reduce(`+`, lapply(list(new_mir_num, new_num),function(x) {x[is.na(x)] <-0;x}))

new_sum <- cbind(new$Gene, new_sum)
new_sum <- cbind(new_mir$miRNA, new_sum)
colnames(new_sum)[1:2] <- c("miRNA", "Gene")

Assignment

After creating the final table, we assign values to them. Firsly, we know that if both are expressed, the assignment should be 1, 0 if neither are expressed. Secondly, if one is expressed, the other is not expressed, the interaction should be assigned a 0. If one of the expression is ? we should assign a ? to the pair interaction. In order to identify it easily, we assign 10 if the ? is observed, and sum the two tables. Finally, we will assign the 0, 1, ? back to them with the following rules: * 0 or 1 or 10 -> 0 * 2 -> 1 * 11 or 20 -> ?

# change 10 to 0
new_sum_copy <- new_sum
new_sum_copy <- new_sum_copy[, -c(1, 2)]

new_sum_copy[new_sum_copy == 1] <- 0
new_sum_copy[new_sum_copy == 10] <- 0

new_sum_copy[new_sum_copy == 2] <- 1

for (i in 1:ncol(new_sum_copy)){
  new_sum_copy[,i]<- (as.character(new_sum_copy[,i]))
}
new_sum_copy[new_sum_copy == "11"] <- "?"
new_sum_copy[new_sum_copy == "20"] <- "?"
